1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,720
 We thank you for this in Jesus' name.

2
00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:04,720
 Everyone says, "Amen, bless you."

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:07,120
 You know, we're in our final week of public faith,

4
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,640
 what it means to live the gospel in the world around us.

5
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:12,240
 And, you know, as a group of pastors,

6
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:14,800
 as we were praying a number of months ago for this series,

7
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
 and we were asking, "What are the topics that's on the Lord's heart?"

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,160
 This one came up that we're speaking about today,

9
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:24,320
 and we're like, "We can't do a series on how we live the gospel publicly

10
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:27,200
 if we don't talk about the reality of our resources in our lives

11
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:31,920
 and the way in which we operate with the resources that God has given us."

12
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,600
 The reality is that one of the most public ways that you will reveal the gospel

13
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:41,920
 to the world around you is how you steward the resources that are in your life.

14
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:46,560
 So whether that's your time, whether that's your energy,

15
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:51,040
 whether that's your finances, whether that's your talents or your gifts,

16
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:54,320
 what you do with what you've been given

17
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:59,600
 reveals to the world the inner values and commitments that you hold.

18
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:04,160
 It's always been said, right, that if you want to find out what's important to someone,

19
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:07,680
 just do an audit of what they spend their time and their money on.

20
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:12,160
 That'll show you pretty quickly what is in the heart and the life of someone.

21
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:17,360
 But I think for us Christians, this area of our resources and what we do with them

22
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:21,040
 is not just an audit of kind of the values within us,

23
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:23,280
 it's actually a question of discipleship.

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,280
 It's actually an invitation into discipleship.

25
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:32,320
 Because what we do with the resources that we have over a period of time as Christians

26
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:35,760
 will become the barometer of our relationship with Jesus.

27
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:40,080
 And over time, it will show the people within our community,

28
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:44,480
 the people outside of that community, the level of submission,

29
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:53,120
 the level of honor, the level of obedience that we have to the one that we seek to proclaim.

30
00:01:54,080 --> 00:02:00,640
 The stewardship of your resources is perhaps the greatest way you reveal to the world around you

31
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:05,520
 the love that you have for a God who has saved, redeemed, and restored you.

32
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:10,320
 There are so many passages in Scripture that speak about this idea of

33
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:12,800
 stewarding the resources God has given us.

34
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,920
 But I want to go to one today that is from the Apostle Peter.

35
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:18,400
 And he's writing to the church.

36
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,080
 This is his first letter.

37
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,320
 And he's writing to his church in a time of persecution,

38
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,920
 a time when the church is struggling.

39
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,600
 And he writes to them and says,

40
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:29,120
 "You've got to understand that you've been saved not just for your little gatherings

41
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,480
 that you have in your house churches,

42
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:34,480
 but you've been saved to bring the message of Christ,

43
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:37,520
 the hope of Jesus, into the world around you."

44
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:42,000
 And he has this list of ways in which we do that.

45
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,040
 And embedded in the middle of it is just this one verse

46
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,880
 where he speaks specifically about the resources in our lives.

47
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:52,160
 Let me read this to you from 1 Peter 4, starting in verse 10.

48
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:57,920
 He says, "Each one of you should use whatever gift that you have received to serve others,

49
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:03,520
 being faithful stewards of God's grace in its various forms."

50
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,400
 I love what Peter does here.

51
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,280
 A very simple sentence, a very simple verse.

52
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,880
 But he starts by saying this.

53
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:14,640
 "Each one of you should use whatever gift that you have received to serve others."

54
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:18,080
 So his starting point is every single one of us has received a gift.

55
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:21,520
 He doesn't say, "Those of you that think you're gifted,

56
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:25,440
 those of you that are wealthy and know that you have a lot of resource."

57
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:31,440
 He says, "Each one of you, regardless of whether you think you have an abundance or not,

58
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:38,160
 should use what it is that God has given you for his glory to serve the people around you."

59
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:41,440
 Which is deeply challenging because I think as Christians,

60
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:45,840
 when we think about the resources in our lives, we have two issues.

61
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:48,880
 We first of all think either we have a lot,

62
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,640
 and that can lead us into a place of poverty,

63
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,480
 and that can lead us into a place of pride.

64
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:56,160
 Or we look at the neighbor next to us and we compare ourselves,

65
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:59,840
 and we find jealousy in us because we think we don't have as much as them.

66
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:04,320
 So when we begin to think about resources in our lives,

67
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:08,800
 often our starting point is either pride or it's jealousy.

68
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,960
 It's either I've got what I need,

69
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:15,200
 or it's kind of comparative or comparison to the one next to me.

70
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,720
 And Peter starts this topic by cutting through all of that.

71
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:21,680
 And he's like, "It's not about how much you have.

72
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,000
 It's about what you do with what you have been given.

73
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,760
 And each one of you has been given something.

74
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:32,800
 And each one of you should administer whatever it is that you've been given

75
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,920
 to serve the people around you."

76
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:40,560
 Notice the language he uses in this verse to highlight this.

77
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,920
 He says "gift." He uses the word "received."

78
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,400
 Later on in the verse, he says "God's grace."

79
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:51,440
 These words are words specifically that Peter is using

80
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:56,000
 to help you to understand that there is a significant mindset shift

81
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,800
 that you need when you become a Christian,

82
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,440
 when it comes to the resources in your life.

83
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:04,400
 He says you've got to understand that this is a gift.

84
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:07,600
 That you have received it.

85
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,320
 And you've received it by God's grace.

86
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:13,520
 So fundamentally, what Peter is teaching here to the church

87
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:17,280
 is that you've got to understand that God is the owner of all things.

88
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,280
 They're all his.

89
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:22,800
 He is sovereign. He's powerful.

90
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,120
 He has control of everything in this world.

91
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,600
 And everything you have is a gift.

92
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,560
 You haven't earned it.

93
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:32,160
 It's not like he's looked down on the vine today and gone,

94
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:34,320
 "Oh, Pastor Andrew, he's in a good place right now.

95
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,680
 I'm going to give him a little bit more."

96
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:40,320
 This is a gift received by God's grace

97
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,880
 because he is the owner of all things.

98
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:46,400
 And that is a deeply important thing for us to be aware of.

99
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,920
 Let me say it in reverse.

100
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,520
 We are not owners.

101
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,280
 Come on, church.

102
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:53,040
 We are not owners.

103
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:57,040
 Which is weird because before we come to Christ,

104
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,960
 that's exactly the mindset that we have.

105
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,760
 Before we have this relationship with Jesus,

106
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,440
 our mindset is always going to be,

107
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:08,800
 "I work hard. I gain. I earn. I control.

108
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:11,760
 It is mine and I get to do what I want with it."

109
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,680
 And so our mindset before we come in a relationship with Jesus

110
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,960
 is, "I'm the owner of everything that I've worked hard for."

111
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,880
 But actually, when we come into faith with Jesus,

112
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,000
 the Bible does not give us an option to think that way anymore.

113
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,920
 The Bible says it's all a 180-degree thought.

114
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:31,760
 Now, no longer am I the owner of everything that I've worked hard for.

115
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:35,200
 Now, I'm a servant of the one who has done it all.

116
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,840
 That it is all in his hands.

117
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:38,800
 He owns it all.

118
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:42,880
 And my relationship now is not, "This is mine because I've gained."

119
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,840
 It is, "This is his, so what do I do with it?"

120
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,520
 Are you with me?

121
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:53,440
 We are not masters of our lives and owners of the things we have

122
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,440
 through our own hard work.

123
00:06:55,440 --> 00:07:00,320
 We are servants of the King and stewards of his resources

124
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,320
 through his divine grace.

125
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,720
 And that changes everything.

126
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:07,520
 That challenges us.

127
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:12,160
 That should light a fire within us.

128
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:16,640
 That we would begin to think of our resources in a different way.

129
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:22,320
 That rather than thinking that we have the responsibility because we own,

130
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:29,200
 we begin to think, "What is it that Jesus would want me to do with this

131
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,520
 because it's not mine anyway?"

132
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:37,840
 When your posture of stewardship is to say, "It's not mine anyway."

133
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:41,440
 The kingdom of God advances.

134
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:45,120
 This is why Peter uses this word here.

135
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,560
 He says, "You are a faithful steward."

136
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:52,400
 The word in the Greek is "oikonomos."

137
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,920
 "Oikonomos" literally translated, "oikos" is house.

138
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:59,120
 "Onomos" is this idea of being a servant.

139
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:04,480
 So, "oikonomos" is basically someone who in the first century was a household manager.

140
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,840
 A household administrator.

141
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:12,400
 And I think it's profound that Peter took this word from the first century

142
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:17,520
 that everybody would have understood as an oikonomos is a household manager.

143
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:21,200
 And he applies it to the resources that we have in our lives from God.

144
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:24,800
 He says, "Don't you realize because he's the owner of all things,

145
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,800
 he's done this profound thing.

146
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:30,000
 He's called you to be his household manager.

147
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:34,400
 To manage and administrate his resources.

148
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:38,240
 Which if I was God, I would not have done it that way."

149
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,960
 I mean, stop for a moment and think about that, right?

150
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:43,920
 Like if you're God and you're like, "Well, I have all this stuff in my life.

151
00:08:43,920 --> 00:08:46,160
 I have all this power and I want to give it away."

152
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:49,600
 And you look at the human beings, you'd be like, "I'm not giving it to those people."

153
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:54,640
 Right? You'd be like, "The sin, the brokenness, the pride, the arrogance."

154
00:08:54,640 --> 00:09:00,160
 But God in his wisdom, a wisdom that we don't always understand,

155
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:04,560
 says, "No, I've placed all of my resources into your hands

156
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,640
 because you are my economists.

157
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:11,040
 I want you to now work that resource out into the world around you."

158
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:16,560
 Notice that the oikonomous word sounds a lot like a modern word we use today,

159
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,160
 which is the word economy.

160
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:23,520
 But actually the word economy draws from this Greek word oikonomous.

161
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:28,240
 So what Peter's teaching is, you've got to understand that when you come to

162
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,040
 faith in Christ Jesus and you look at all the resources in your life,

163
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,600
 you are then swept up in a new economy.

164
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:39,600
 It's not the old economy where you can hoard and receive and do what you want with it.

165
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,800
 It's a new economy.

166
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:44,640
 And in God's economy, he's looking for his people to release

167
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:49,520
 that there would be a flow of that resource in the kingdom.

168
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:55,360
 This concept of the flow of resource is central to the idea of what it means

169
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:58,560
 for us to be stewards and household managers.

170
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:04,160
 And that we are to do this in beautiful kingdom revealing ways.

171
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:07,840
 This is the image of the first church, is it not, in the book of Acts,

172
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:13,600
 who as they begin to wrestle with the profundity of Jesus's death and resurrection,

173
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:17,520
 begin to create communities all around the Greco-Roman empire

174
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:22,480
 that would reveal the gospel, reveal a new economy to the world around it.

175
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:26,480
 I mean, take a look at Acts chapter 2, verses 44 and 45.

176
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:32,720
 It says this, it says, "All the believers were together and had everything in common.

177
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:37,040
 They sold property and possessions to give to anyone who had need."

178
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:39,040
 This is a new economy at work.

179
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:42,720
 And it's at work because these Christians have begun to understand

180
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:45,280
 they're no longer the owners, but they are stewards.

181
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:48,880
 And because they're stewards, then the flow of those resources

182
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:53,760
 needs to move out from them into the world around them.

183
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:57,760
 Anybody who had need within their community was met

184
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:02,080
 through the flow of God's stewards within the church.

185
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,440
 Such a beautiful picture.

186
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:06,480
 And think about the implications of this.

187
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:12,800
 Abundance, this generosity, which is really the overflow

188
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:16,000
 of the resources of God in the world, and poverty,

189
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,680
 which is the restriction of those resources

190
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:22,720
 and actually the inequitable distribution of them.

191
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:28,880
 Both generosity and poverty flow from the gateway of stewardship.

192
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:34,560
 Which means that if we are the economists of God's household,

193
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:37,760
 we as Christians are responsible for whether there might be

194
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:40,960
 a generous flow of those resources in our communities,

195
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:46,880
 or there might be a poverty type restriction of those resources in our communities.

196
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:49,360
 And we're not just talking about the church, we're talking about our city.

197
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:55,040
 And as we take on board that incredible responsibility,

198
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:57,200
 it should shake something within us.

199
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:03,680
 It's why Peter says here, you are to use this economic gift

200
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:07,360
 that you have to flow those resources to serve others.

201
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:12,560
 Now, that doesn't mean that you can't be a steward of those resources

202
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:14,800
 in a way that can benefit yourself.

203
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:21,120
 But the Bible is trying to challenge us to think about this idea of generosity,

204
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:27,040
 and poverty, and which of these two do I generally do in the world around me?

205
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:33,120
 In other words, am I flowing the resource as a river, or have I become a dam?

206
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:37,680
 Have I backed up those resources?

207
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:41,680
 Are those resources building up behind the walls of my fear,

208
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:47,360
 the walls of my pride, the walls of my greed?

209
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:51,920
 Have I become a dam for the flow of God's resources in the world,

210
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:57,600
 or am I a river which is releasing and watering the world around me

211
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:01,120
 with the beautiful things that Christ has done for me?

212
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:03,680
 This is a deep challenge.

213
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:08,080
 And this is why Peter says these words.

214
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:12,640
 He says, you're not just a steward, but you must be a faithful steward.

215
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:17,200
 Peter understood that a stewardship mentality is not enough.

216
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,560
 You have to steward with a faithfulness,

217
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:24,480
 with this sense that you understand what is on God's heart,

218
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:28,560
 and you want to administer that in the world so that the gospel might be revealed.

219
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:34,160
 You see, just having a stewardship mentality does not guarantee

220
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:37,200
 that you will become a vessel of the flow of God's resources in the world.

221
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:42,640
 You've got to take that mentality and link it to this idea of faithfulness.

222
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:45,760
 And faithfulness, I think, is linked to two things.

223
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:50,400
 First of all, it's linked to the idea of being obedient with what God has given us.

224
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:54,240
 It doesn't mean that you have to take a vow of poverty.

225
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,760
 Being faithful to the stewardship of God's resources in your life

226
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:02,160
 might mean taking care of your family, making sure your family has what it needs.

227
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:04,800
 It's not saying that you have to become poor.

228
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:08,160
 But equally, it's not saying that you have to become rich.

229
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:11,840
 It's not saying that suddenly, as a good faithful steward,

230
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,320
 God's going to keep rewarding you and rewarding you and rewarding you

231
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,760
 so you can become wealthier and wealthier.

232
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:19,360
 This is not a prosperity gospel-centered idea.

233
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:26,000
 In fact, what Peter is saying is, whether you're poor or you're wealthy,

234
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,960
 God is saying the same thing to you.

235
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:33,440
 God speaks exactly the same thing to the poorest of the poor

236
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,040
 and the wealthiest of the wealthy.

237
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,640
 He asks them the same question.

238
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:37,760
 Here's the question.

239
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:41,760
 Are you being faithful with the resource that God has given you?

240
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:47,120
 You see, faithfulness is not linked to abundance.

241
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,720
 It's linked to obedience.

242
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:54,640
 And so those who don't seem to have much and those that seem to have a lot

243
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:57,840
 are asked that question.

244
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:01,200
 Are we still being faithful with what it is that we have received?

245
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:05,760
 Are we flowing the resource that God has placed within us?

246
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:13,280
 This is why when the Bible speaks about the resources that he gives to his church,

247
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:17,120
 it doesn't speak about it primarily as a theoretical issue.

248
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:20,240
 It's not spoken about primarily as a theological issue.

249
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:23,680
 It's spoken primarily as a relational issue.

250
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:29,360
 In other words, my relationship with the owner of all things

251
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:34,240
 will have a direct dependency on how I steward those resources.

252
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:39,120
 How I see Jesus is going to impact what I do with his resources.

253
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,840
 Does that make sense?

254
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:45,920
 So as my intimacy and my knowledge and my connection with Jesus increases,

255
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:51,680
 so should the resources of him flow out from me in ways that reveal the gospel around me.

256
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:57,920
 But equally, if that relationship is stale, if it's become stagnant,

257
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:02,400
 if it's broken because of sin or broken because of whatever it might be,

258
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:07,680
 then I don't become a vessel by which I might be able to use those resources

259
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:09,680
 in the way that would honor the owner.

260
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:15,040
 This is exactly the teaching that Jesus gives us in the parable of the talent

261
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,120
 in Matthew 25 verses 14 to 30.

262
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:19,520
 We don't have time to look at it line by line today,

263
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:22,400
 but let me just summarize the parable itself.

264
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:26,320
 There is a wealthy home owner who's going on a trip

265
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:30,720
 and actually gives his property to be cared for in his absence

266
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:34,560
 to three oikonomists in his midst, household managers.

267
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:38,720
 Two of them take what is received from the master of the house

268
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,560
 and they put that money to work.

269
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,240
 They know him.

270
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,520
 They know what he would want.

271
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:46,640
 They understand his expectations and they put that money to work.

272
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:49,680
 And when the master of the house returns, they show,

273
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:52,720
 "Look, we've doubled what it is that you have given us."

274
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:56,320
 And the household master looks at what they've done

275
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:58,880
 knowing that it is in connection to his character

276
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:05,360
 and speaks over them, "Well done, my good and faithful servants.

277
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:09,520
 You've proven a faithfulness because you knew me."

278
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:15,520
 The third oikonomist, though, didn't know the master very well.

279
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:18,480
 In fact, was only afraid of the master.

280
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,440
 So fearful, in fact, that he was like, "Well, if I invest this money

281
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:24,000
 and I get it wrong and I lose the money, then I'm going to get punished."

282
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:28,320
 So he takes the gift that he had been given, buries it in the ground,

283
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:30,240
 just waiting for the master to return.

284
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,520
 When the master returns, uncovers it and brings it to the master.

285
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,040
 And the master is like, "What have you done?"

286
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:38,640
 And the response is, "Well, I thought you were like this.

287
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,440
 I feared you.

288
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:42,000
 I thought you were going to tell me off if I got it wrong."

289
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,400
 So then the master is like, "You have no idea who I am.

290
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,600
 Because if you knew my character, if you knew my heart,

291
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:51,040
 you would have at least put it into the bank and earned some interest on it."

292
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,800
 He literally says that.

293
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,040
 And he says, "So therefore,"

294
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,800
 he doesn't say, "Well done, my good and faithful servant."

295
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:57,600
 He says, "No, no."

296
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:00,400
 Actually, there's some of the things that he says are pretty strong in the Scripture.

297
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:06,480
 And it's like he gets sort of chastised because he didn't know him.

298
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:09,920
 And so when Peter is speaking to the church about this idea of,

299
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:13,200
 "Hey, you're a faithful steward of the resources God has given you."

300
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,960
 I think he's thinking about the parable of talents.

301
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:18,240
 And he's saying, "That means you've got to know the one who is the owner of it all.

302
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:24,240
 And as your heart increases in that, your hands will open even more."

303
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:28,000
 The more that we understand the heart and the nature of God,

304
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,840
 the more we will be faithful with the resources that He has given us.

305
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,760
 That's just the reality of it all.

306
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,160
 So how do we do this?

307
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:40,000
 How do we as Christians honor the owner of all things

308
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:45,520
 with the faithfulness of a stewardship of the resources that He's placed in our lives,

309
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:49,200
 whether those resources may seem to us a lot or a little?

310
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,480
 How do we do it faithfully?

311
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:54,000
 Well, there's this beautiful passage in the Old Testament,

312
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,840
 in the book of Ecclesiastes, actually.

313
00:18:55,840 --> 00:19:00,000
 And oftentimes when I've spoken on stewardship, I've gone to this passage.

314
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 So if you've been at the Vine for a while,

315
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,440
 you're probably going to roll your eyes now

316
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,760
 because I'm going back to that passage again.

317
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:10,240
 But I think it's actually one of the most beautiful demonstrations

318
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:13,120
 of what stewardship of resource really looks like

319
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:16,960
 and what Peter is teaching about in 1 Peter 4.10.

320
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:20,000
 So this is Ecclesiastes chapter 4,

321
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,280
 a wisdom writer who's writing truths about the world.

322
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:25,280
 And he says this, he says,

323
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:28,800
 "The fool folds his hands and ruins himself.

324
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:31,680
 Better one handful with tranquility

325
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,960
 than two handfuls with toil and chasing after the wind."

326
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:40,240
 It's classic wisdom, kind of poetic structure to this verse.

327
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:43,600
 The writer is challenging his people.

328
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:47,280
 The broader context of the chapter is he's talking specifically about what we have,

329
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,280
 the resources in our lives.

330
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:52,000
 He says, "The fool folds his hands.

331
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,560
 Better one handful with tranquility

332
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:58,000
 than two handfuls with toil and chasing after the wind."

333
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,680
 Let me show you a bit of a demonstration of what I think actually

334
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:04,800
 the wisdom writer here is trying to communicate

335
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:09,120
 through the Hebrew word that is used here in the structure of the passage.

336
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:12,320
 So I want you to think, this is a box of rice.

337
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:16,080
 I want you to think about this box of rice as the resources in your life,

338
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:20,400
 like your energy, your time, your finances, your talents, your gifts,

339
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,440
 whatever they might be.

340
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:26,720
 This represents the fullness of those resources that God has given to you.

341
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:29,120
 The wisdom writer says, "You're a fool."

342
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:32,160
 The Hebrew means you're basically an idiot.

343
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:35,520
 If you recognize that you have all these resources

344
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,120
 and you fold your hands to them.

345
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:39,920
 In other words, you don't do anything with it.

346
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:45,360
 This is the posture of that third servant in the parable of the talents.

347
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:48,000
 It's like I've got all this resource that has been given to me,

348
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,960
 but I just fold my hands and I check out.

349
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,960
 And I don't do anything with it.

350
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:56,480
 You might be sitting there thinking like, "Well, that's a bit silly.

351
00:20:56,480 --> 00:21:00,080
 Why would anyone ever not do something with what they have been given?"

352
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:02,880
 But I wonder whether you just take a moment to reflect about

353
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:08,160
 why maybe all of us at some point folds our hands to the resources God has given us.

354
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:11,440
 I think we fold our hands sometimes out of fear.

355
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:15,200
 Fear that if we did something with those resources,

356
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:19,280
 we might lose them entirely and we don't want to lose them.

357
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,880
 So we fold our hands and check out.

358
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:25,280
 I think sometimes we fold our hands because maybe in the past

359
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:27,200
 we did something with our resource.

360
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:31,040
 Maybe our energy or our time or we connected in a relationship

361
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:34,080
 or we gave everything to someone and they turned their back on us.

362
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:37,920
 They betrayed us or they hurt us deeply.

363
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:42,320
 And because of that hurt and that pain, we're like, "I'm never going to do that again.

364
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:46,000
 I'm never going to give anybody my time like that again."

365
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:50,240
 And so out of hurt, we fold our hands.

366
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:53,760
 I think the other reason why we do it is out of insecurity.

367
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:59,120
 We compare our gifts, our resources to what somebody else has.

368
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:01,920
 And we think, "Well, the church doesn't need that gift of mine

369
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,440
 because have you seen that person?

370
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:06,320
 Or my talent doesn't seem to be as great as that.

371
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:08,000
 Or my resources are not as much."

372
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:14,160
 And so because of an insecurity that's driven by comparison, we fold our hands.

373
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:18,160
 The wisdom writer says, "If you're doing that, you're an idiot."

374
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:20,720
 But then he says this.

375
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:26,640
 He says, "You're also a bit of an idiot if you take two handfuls."

376
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:30,640
 He says, "Two handfuls is a toil and a chasing after the wind."

377
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:33,680
 In the Hebrew, the word for hand in this part of the passage

378
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,600
 is actually the Hebrew word "khofen."

379
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:40,800
 And "khofen" means literally to clench your hand, to grasp a hold of.

380
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,840
 So the wisdom writer is saying, "You are also a fool

381
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:49,440
 if you grasp a hold of those resources and you hold onto them as tightly as you can.

382
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,280
 You khofen the resource."

383
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:55,600
 Now on the surface, we look at this and we think, "But isn't that a good thing?"

384
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,960
 I mean, we haven't folded our hands.

385
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:57,840
 We haven't checked out.

386
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:02,720
 We've taken the resource that God has given us and we're holding it tightly.

387
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,640
 And sometimes I think we kid ourselves.

388
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:07,600
 It's like, "I'm holding it tightly until God tells me to do something with it."

389
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,480
 But actually, we're just hoping that God never speaks to us

390
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:15,840
 and that we can just continue to hold on to the two great handfuls of resource that we've got.

391
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:18,000
 I want you to notice two things.

392
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:22,400
 Number one, it's really hard when you're grasping a hold of the resources

393
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:28,480
 God has given you in your life, like khofen, to get more of that resource into your hands.

394
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:31,920
 I mean, I'd have to change the posture of my hand to be able to do so.

395
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,920
 Notice also that it's hard to let it flow.

396
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:40,400
 If I grasp it tightly, it's not falling out of my hands, perhaps like it should.

397
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:47,920
 The wisdom writer is saying, "The posture of this is toil and chasing after the wind."

398
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:50,720
 This is anxiety and stress.

399
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,800
 This is a poverty mentality.

400
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,800
 I'm not going to lose what it is.

401
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,480
 I don't want to lose what I've got.

402
00:23:56,480 --> 00:24:00,960
 And in the stress and the toil, we grasp a hold even tighter.

403
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:07,040
 And we say things like, "When my bank account gets to this level, I'll be more generous."

404
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:13,760
 And then when we get there, we're like, "Yeah, but I just got more expenses now as well.

405
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:17,760
 So maybe it's okay for me to wait again."

406
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:24,080
 I think all of us resonate with the stress and the anxiety and the toil of khofen.

407
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:28,320
 We may have two big handfuls, but it's killing us.

408
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:34,160
 So the wisdom writer is saying, "There's a better way to posture your heart when it comes

409
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:36,160
 to the resources of God's kingdom."

410
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:40,080
 He says, "It's better to have just one handful, but with tranquility."

411
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:43,840
 The Hebrew word for handful here is chof.

412
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:49,120
 Chof literally means an open hand, a palm facing upwards.

413
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:55,120
 So rather than these two grasping hands of posture of heart, he's saying, "It's better

414
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,000
 to be like this.

415
00:24:56,000 --> 00:25:00,880
 It's better to have one hand open before him, like this."

416
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:05,840
 Now, you'll notice that the resources is flowing just like Peter would hope that it

417
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:06,400
 would flow.

418
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:10,160
 But if you're anything like me, you're seeing the resources coming out of your bank account

419
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:12,480
 or out of your energy, and you're like, "Hang on a sec.

420
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,680
 There's not a lot of resource left."

421
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:18,800
 But notice what happens when your posture is like this, God can do this.

422
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:23,440
 Because God can put in and flow and in and flow.

423
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:25,920
 And this, my friends, is the flow of the kingdom.

424
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,720
 This is what the resources are supposed to do.

425
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:34,400
 The Bible writer says, "Oh, man, it is better to be like this and to have tranquility in

426
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:39,040
 your life, receiving and flowing, receiving and flowing."

427
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:44,720
 Peter writes to the church, and he says, "Be a faithful steward of God's grace that he's

428
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,680
 given to you.

429
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:49,120
 It is not to fold and give up, to grasp tightly.

430
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:54,480
 It is literally to just be open-handed before him."

431
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:56,800
 This, my friends, is peace.

432
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,800
 It's life.

433
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:04,240
 It's the way God's economy was always designed to be.

434
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:11,360
 A few weeks ago, we were having a staff devotion, and somebody shared a story, a testimony of

435
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,040
 one of our community members here at the Vine.

436
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:17,920
 And I was so blown away by this that I was like, "We have to make space in our service

437
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:24,000
 today to hear of this," because it's a story about the flow of God's resources within its

438
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:24,560
 kingdom.

439
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:29,440
 So I wonder whether you put your hands together as we invite Pastor Stephen and Minaj to come

440
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:29,920
 to the stage.

441
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:37,920
 Can we do that?

442
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:45,440
 Thanks, Andrew.

443
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:47,520
 Good morning, everybody.

444
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:54,000
 Just before we start, I just want to just clarify something.

445
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,240
 A lot of people are a little bit confused about what's ARISE and what's BOH, so I just want

446
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,120
 to clarify that.

447
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:02,160
 So ARISE is a ministry in the Vine Church.

448
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:06,880
 BOH is an NGO that operates alongside the Vine Church.

449
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:13,600
 We serve a part of the same community, but the way we kind of figure out who does what

450
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:21,040
 in taking care of kind of a holistic perspective of meeting everybody's needs, BOH focuses

451
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:26,240
 on the hand needs, the felt needs, and we focus on the heart needs, the spiritual needs.

452
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:33,120
 So just to clarify that a little bit, I know a lot of people think ARISE is BOH or BOH is

453
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,840
 ARISE, but actually we're two separate things.

454
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:38,000
 So welcome, Minaj.

455
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,280
 Good to have you with us today.

456
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:44,880
 I wonder, I know you've been in Hong Kong and around the Vine for about 10 years.

457
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:50,320
 Can you maybe just give us a brief introduction to your background and how you got here?

458
00:27:52,800 --> 00:28:05,040
 Yes, I'm originally from India, and I grew up in a very strict Hindu family.

459
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:16,800
 And in my early 20s, I believed in science rather than God.

460
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:31,120
 And due to some trouble in my country, I had to come to Hong Kong as an asylum seeker.

461
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:47,760
 So after I arrived in Hong Kong, like two weeks, one of my friends invited me to the

462
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:50,720
 Vine Church.

463
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:56,000
 It was a Sunday, so I had nothing else to do.

464
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,960
 So I said, "Let's go."

465
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:23,200
 So one of my first visits, I came up for the prayer, and the person asked me what I wanted

466
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:23,920
 to pray for.

467
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:39,520
 So even though at that time I had many material needs, but I found myself asking, "Please

468
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:42,880
 pray for me to come closer to God."

469
00:29:46,240 --> 00:30:07,840
 And every time when I come to the Vine, I felt amazing peace, but I had never felt before.

470
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:18,400
 And later I baptized—I remember my new birthday is 12th of June, 2016.

471
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,440
 Wow, that's awesome.

472
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,640
 That's awesome.

473
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:26,880
 So Pastor Andrew's been speaking to us today about stewardship and this idea of God's

474
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:32,880
 resources are meant to flow through us, kind of being a river or a conduit for His resources

475
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,280
 rather than holding onto stuff and being like a dam.

476
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:42,000
 So I know part of your story, there's one incident that happened in your life where

477
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:45,520
 something flowed into your life and God blessed you in a way.

478
00:30:45,520 --> 00:30:47,200
 Can you tell us about that?

479
00:30:47,200 --> 00:31:02,160
 Yes, at the very beginning in Hong Kong, for some reason I lost all my belongings, especially

480
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:02,660
 clothes.

481
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:11,300
 One of my friends gave me a trouser, but it was too big, too loose.

482
00:31:11,300 --> 00:31:13,300
 I cannot walk.

483
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:18,500
 If I walk a few steps, I need to hold or otherwise I had to adjust.

484
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:29,540
 So in desperation, I went to a nearby shop here to buy a belt to fix it.

485
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:41,460
 I found a nice belt, but I didn't have enough money to buy it.

486
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:53,940
 I tried to negotiate with the shopkeeper, but the shopkeeper wouldn't budge on the

487
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:54,500
 price.

488
00:31:54,500 --> 00:32:00,180
 I was really heartbroken.

489
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:07,540
 I left the shop and I found myself holding the handrail beside the road.

490
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:23,780
 Inside I was crying and I closed my eyes and I asked, "Lord, God, how long will you

491
00:32:23,780 --> 00:32:24,340
 test me?"

492
00:32:24,340 --> 00:32:33,220
 And the next day we had ARISE fellowship.

493
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:52,420
 Unexpectedly, an Indonesian sister approached me with a plastic bag and she handed me the

494
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:55,940
 plastic bag and said, "This is for you."

495
00:32:55,940 --> 00:33:07,940
 When I opened the bag, I was astonished to see inside it was a leather belt inside.

496
00:33:07,940 --> 00:33:19,780
 And curiously I asked, "How do you know I needed a belt?"

497
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:42,820
 And she said she was shopping the day before and suddenly my face popped up in her mind

498
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:52,500
 and she felt that God was prompting her to buy a belt for me.

499
00:33:58,100 --> 00:34:14,740
 And then later I found out it was the same time when I cried out to the Lord to ask him

500
00:34:14,740 --> 00:34:17,540
 for a belt for my problem.

501
00:34:24,820 --> 00:34:47,940
 Because this incident profoundly changed me and I also want to be grateful for how she

502
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:57,540
 blessed me even though she had not much money because she was the same as an asylum seeker

503
00:34:57,540 --> 00:34:58,260
 like me.

504
00:34:58,260 --> 00:35:12,820
 But she was obedient and faithful and her faithfulness also guided me.

505
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:25,060
 I also want to follow her example to bless and help others.

506
00:35:25,620 --> 00:35:26,120
 Wow.

507
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:31,860
 And you have been a tremendous blessing to so many people here at the Vine Church and

508
00:35:31,860 --> 00:35:35,140
 in Arise Ministry and I know that's definitely part of your heart.

509
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:42,500
 But I know there's a very specific thing that the Lord asked you to do and you've

510
00:35:42,500 --> 00:35:45,220
 been doing this for like seven to eight years now.

511
00:35:45,220 --> 00:35:46,900
 Can you tell us a little bit about that?

512
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:50,280
 Yes.

513
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:55,800
 The Lord blessed me in many ways.

514
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:56,300
 Yeah.

515
00:35:56,300 --> 00:36:01,240
 So I have received so much from the Lord.

516
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:08,840
 I was thinking I want to give back.

517
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:29,000
 At the same time, the Branches of Hope launched a campaign to give us like a piggy bank, this

518
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:29,800
 piggy bank.

519
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:31,320
 This is Manoj's piggy bank.

520
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:42,520
 To collect the changes and bring the end of the year to donate to BOH.

521
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:49,320
 But I want to participate.

522
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:55,480
 I am thinking how can I participate?

523
00:36:58,040 --> 00:37:02,920
 So I prayed to God and asked, "Please guide me."

524
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:06,920
 And God showed me like a...

525
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:16,680
 I have decided to put one dollar every day in my piggy bank.

526
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:17,980
 Yeah.

527
00:37:17,980 --> 00:37:20,280
 There's money in there.

528
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:29,160
 So end of the year, $365 I gave to the BOH.

529
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:29,660
 Yeah.

530
00:37:29,660 --> 00:37:37,560
 So I must be honest with my...

531
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:45,800
 Because sometime I had no money to recharge my Octopus card.

532
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,300
 Yeah.

533
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:51,640
 So I need to borrow from the piggy bank.

534
00:37:52,120 --> 00:37:54,520
 I think we've all been there, right?

535
00:37:54,520 --> 00:38:07,400
 But I always like made sure to end of every year, I made like $365.

536
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,860
 Wow.

537
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:15,000
 So I am still doing this day.

538
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:17,640
 So I don't know if you heard the last part.

539
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:21,720
 He said this started in 2018 and he's still doing it today as you can hear.

540
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:23,880
 So thank you so much, Monoj.

541
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:26,200
 That's such an amazing testimony.

542
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:27,800
 Yeah, let's give him a round of applause.

543
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:34,680
 And your faithfulness and your obedience to the Lord is an example to all of us.

544
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:37,320
 So thank you very much for sharing that with us today.

545
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:37,960
 God bless you.

546
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:49,000
 I think the Lord sees something like that and sort of turns to Monoj and says,

547
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:52,680
 "Well done, my good and faithful servant."

548
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:53,180
 Amen.

549
00:38:53,180 --> 00:38:59,560
 And Peter writes to the church and he goes, "Each one of you have a gift

550
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:03,080
 and you are to faithfully administrate that gift to serve others,

551
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:09,000
 being a faithful steward of God's grace that has been entrusted to you in all of its forms."

552
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:09,960
 We're not owners.

553
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:11,880
 We're stewards.

554
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:17,800
 We receive such abundance and we've been given such glorious grace.

555
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:21,080
 Peter would say, "It is in your hands."

556
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:25,400
 The question for us then is, are those hands folded?

557
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,920
 Are they clenched?

558
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:28,440
 Are they open?

559
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:30,120
 Can I pray for you?

560
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:31,720
 Should we stand together?

561
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:32,200
 Let's pray.

562
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:40,120
 Father, I'm just so grateful for each person in this room and watching online

563
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,800
 and our overflow in this moment.

564
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:47,960
 Lord, you called us to be these stewards of the resources you have planted and placed in our lives.

565
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:53,960
 What a joy it is to be able to stand before you as not owners,

566
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:59,240
 those responsibly entrusted as household managers.

567
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:04,360
 Lord, we pray that we would be able to manage your resources effectively for your glory.

568
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:10,360
 Lord, where fear has gotten away, would you just speak to us?

569
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:18,600
 Lord, where insecurity has played a part in us holding on, would you forgive us?

570
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:24,360
 Lord, for those of us in this room that recognize we've become a dam rather than a flowing river,

571
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:29,160
 would you help us to understand why and would you enable us to let go?

572
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:37,480
 For those of us that resonate with the two fists clenched and the stress and the fear

573
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:45,720
 and the anxiety that comes alongside of those two clenched fists, Lord, would your spirit fill us now

574
00:40:45,720 --> 00:40:51,480
 and bring that tranquility, that peace that needs to be over us?

575
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:57,560
 And would you help us to open our hand before you, that palm open,

576
00:40:58,680 --> 00:41:01,320
 enabling the resource to flow for your kingdom?

577
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:06,440
 And God, what a beautiful thing it is to be Christians in Hong Kong that could

578
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:11,160
 model a different economy to the world's economy, to Hong Kong's economy.

579
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:16,120
 That it wouldn't be about hoarding and gaining and status and showing.

580
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:23,400
 It would be about liberating and giving and letting go and glorifying Jesus.

581
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:29,800
 And as Menage has so beautifully shown us, as he received, so he eagerly gave.

582
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:36,920
 Would that be upon us all as we head out to be those public witnesses of the gospel

583
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:40,120
 in the spheres of influence you planted us in?

584
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:43,240
 And we give you glory for this in Jesus' name.

585
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:45,080
 Everyone says, Amen.

586
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:45,400
 Amen.

587
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,320
 Let's worship together.

588
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:53,640
 Amen.

589
00:41:53,640 --> 00:41:55,640
 (music)

